404
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:52,920
Let's have a drink.

405
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:53,800
Let's drink.

406
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:54,480
Sure.

407
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:55,440
Here.

408
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:57,720
Which type do you like?

409
00:16:57,720 --> 00:17:00,000
You're so troublesome.

410
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:02,840
[Crossroad Bistro]

411
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:07,760
A dish ordered in-store was sent back yesterday.

412
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:08,720
Yi Dang.

413
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:10,000
It was my fault.

414
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,520
I mistook a medium-rare steak and rice

415
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:12,480
as a medium.

416
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:13,640
Consider it my fault.

417
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:14,599
It's okay.

418
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,079
Don't do it again.

419
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:18,079
Xi,

420
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:19,760
a vase was broken in the private room last night.

421
00:17:20,079 --> 00:17:20,920
I know.

422
00:17:21,079 --> 00:17:22,800
A kid accidentally broke it when running around.

423
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:24,060
The customer has compensated us.

424
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:26,680
Have you written the discounted dish for today?

425
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:27,359
Not yet.

426
00:17:27,359 --> 00:17:28,280
I'll do it now.

427
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:32,200
What was it? Abalone Sauce Dish and...

428
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,480
Assorted Mushrooms.

429
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:35,400
That's a good match.

430
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:36,800
Can't you remember it?

431
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:37,960
You need to ask every time.

432
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:41,200
Anything sold out?

433
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:42,320
Not yet.

434
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,000
OK.

435
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,360
Any other problems, everyone?

436
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:47,640
Did we get rid of the bad review from the day before?

437
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,440
We have apologized.

438
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:51,720
The customer hasn't replied.

439
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:52,560
What then?

440
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:53,840
Nothing happened.

441
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:55,200
Never mind.

442
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:56,640
Get prepared, guys.

443
00:17:56,880 --> 00:17:57,400
Today...

444
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:58,400
Do you know that

445
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:00,840
these deliberate bad reviews can 
 destroy a restaurant?

446
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:02,690
Nan,

447
00:18:02,690 --> 00:18:03,940
I don't think we did anything wrong.

448
00:18:03,940 --> 00:18:06,350
When he placed the order, 
 we asked him if there's anything he doesn't eat.

449
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:06,910
He denied.

450
00:18:06,910 --> 00:18:08,800
After we served fried black tiger shrimp with garlic,

451
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:10,690
he said he doesn't eat garlic and demanded to 
 return the dish.

452
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:11,400
Wasn't that nonsense?

453
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,320
Yeah.

454
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:13,600
I just pointed out

455
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,400
that he didn't say it in the beginning.

456
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:16,200
He said

457
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,110
"Never mind. Leave it here."

458
00:18:17,110 --> 00:18:18,460
And immediately wrote a bad review,

459
00:18:18,460 --> 00:18:19,890
saying that we have bad service attitudes.

460
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:20,360
Stop it.

461
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:21,000
It's not us.

462
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:21,680
It's you.

463
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:23,880
What's wrong with my attitude?

464
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,280
Why did you reason with him?

465
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:26,960
Just say sorry

466
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:28,240
and send the dish back.

467
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:30,680
He didn't make it clear,

468
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:32,200
why should we pay for that?

469
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,080
Ms. Feng,

470
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:34,680
can you calculate?

471
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,040
Do you know how many customers

472
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:37,480
you will lose because of a bad review?

473
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:39,240
How much does a dish cost?

474
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:42,320
Tell me.

475
00:18:42,320 --> 00:18:43,280
What should I do?

476
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:44,720
Contact him in private.

477
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:46,600
Coupons.

478
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:47,840
Discounts.

479
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:49,280
Free dishes.

480
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:50,520
I'll let you decide.

481
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,320
If you say so,

482
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:53,480
anyone can write a bad review

483
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:54,520
and dine and dash.

484
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:56,600
I'm not trying to argue with you.

485
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:58,040
We are open for business.

486
00:18:58,040 --> 00:18:59,480
We're bound to see all kinds of people.

487
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,520
We aim to earn money,

488
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:03,080
not to dwell on the morality of customers.

489
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:08,000
Alright.

490
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:10,360
I won't repeat today's tasks.

491
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:11,720
Work hard, everyone.

492
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:13,840
Try to break the record again at the end of the month.

493
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:16,920
20 minutes to go before we start the service at 11:00.

494
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:18,360
Don't slack.

495
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:20,440
Alright?

496
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:21,320
You're dismissed.

497
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:25,600
Hello. May I ask who's in charge?

498
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:26,560
I am.

499
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:28,640
May I ask who you are?

500
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:30,660
We are from the Office of Emergency Management.

501
00:19:30,660 --> 00:19:31,760
We want to have a look around.

502
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:32,400
Go on.

503
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:34,160
Show us the kitchen first.

504
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:34,960
Sure.

505
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:40,480
Wait a moment, please.

506
00:19:43,080 --> 00:19:44,840
This is against the regulation.

507
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:47,560
What's wrong with this?

508
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:50,040
Are there any other fire exits in your restaurant?

509
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:50,960
No.

510
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:53,040
Then you have to change the stairs into a ramp.

511
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,120
A ramp?

512
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:57,400
Then customers and staff

513
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,440
will easily trip over.

514
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,020
Listen to me.

515
00:19:59,020 --> 00:20:00,120
According to the regulations,

516
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:00,790
fire exits

517
00:20:00,790 --> 00:20:01,810
need to have accessibility.

518
00:20:01,810 --> 00:20:02,570
If there's a fire,

519
00:20:02,570 --> 00:20:03,470
fire-fighting equipment

520
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:04,760
needs to go through without any problem.

521
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:05,880
It's a potential safety hazard.

522
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:06,880
What if customers trip over?

523
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,240
That's a potential safety hazard, too.

524
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:09,600
We regret to inform you

525
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:11,080
that you have to cooperate with us.

526
00:20:11,080 --> 00:20:12,610
You have to shut down until changing this.

527
00:20:12,610 --> 00:20:13,240
Shut down?

528
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:14,920
Why are you finding fault with us?

529
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:16,160
They're just two or three staircases.

530
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:18,200
You can lift practically any equipment 
 with these stairs.

531
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,400
Why do you accuse us?

532
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:20,570
Who is finding fault with you?

533
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:21,600
Sir, Madam.

534
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:22,960
It's hot.

535
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:24,600
Drink some water and don't be angry.

536
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,200
You're right.

537
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,240
It's our responsibility.

538
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:26,660
We will

539
00:20:26,660 --> 00:20:27,810
rectify and improve it right away.

540
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:28,600
We don't need water.

541
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:29,960
Please do understand that

542
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,120
our duty

543
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:32,560
is to keep everyone safe.

544
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:34,000
We do.

545
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,280
We'll do it right now.

546
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:35,960
OK.

547
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:38,040
Our number is on the notice.

548
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:39,520
Call us when you finish it.

549
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:40,320
OK.

550
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:41,160
Let's go.

551
00:20:41,520 --> 00:20:42,200
Alright.

552
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,200
Madam.

553
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:43,960
Safe journey.

554
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:00,720
Are you stupid?

555
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:02,880
They were bullying us.

556
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:03,920
Feng Xi.

557
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:06,240
Do you have a delusional disorder of being prosecuted?

558
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:08,040
It's their job.

559
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:09,440
Everything they said makes sense.

560
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:10,560
When they find the problem,

561
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:12,680
we have to figure out a way to deal with it.

562
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:15,280
Why did you get so emotional and argue so much?

563
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,760
Why aren't you working?

564
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:24,320
What's left to do when we are shut down?'

565
00:21:32,360 --> 00:21:33,360
We need to

566
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:34,560
ask Yu Songyang to solve this.

567
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:36,440
Why do you need him?

568
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,160
He's a designer,

569
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:39,080
not a foreman.

570
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:41,800
Then I'll call You Shanshan

571
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:42,800
and ask her to solve it.

572
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:46,320
Can you not turn to her whenever tiny problems occur?

573
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:47,960
What's the point of you being the manager?

574
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:51,120
Who should I ask for help to solve this?

575
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:52,520
Me.

576
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:53,880
We're shut down now.

577
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:54,960
